Bakal's tenant: The stoves are heating up, he signed a higher rent.
An imposing elderly man walked out the door of the customer center of the company RPG Byty of the "baron of coal" Zdenek Bakal, the largest private owner of apartments for rent in the Czech Republic.
He had under his arm a file with three new rental contracts for three apartments: his own, his daughter’s and his son’s, who is serving a sentence.
The deregulation has increased the rent for these three people.
Instead of paying 3500 the son will have to pay from next year for a 2+1 apartment of second category 4100 crowns.
"And there is no hot water and the heating works with solid fuel," he points to the new contract of his son the man who has the power to sign.
"But I signed anyway," he explained, angry and half resigned.
The BytyOKD.cz citizen association, which described the new rental conditions as "immoral and indecent", advises tenants not to sign and wait until December 7, when a notice will be published to explain the method to be followed to claim.
But the man reacts to this with a gesture of the hand.
"One says this, the other says something else" with frowns.
The Ostrava region becomes the laboratory of deregulation.
After New Year's Eve, this is what most apartments in the Czech Republic expect, whose rents do not correspond to the market price.
For this reason Aktualne.cz has decided to personally visit the "laboratory".
The RPG waiting room on Havirovska Street is one of four in the Ostrava region and is already full on Tuesday at 09:00 a.m.
Right next to the door stands a security company guard with a device to call customers.
A special button, "rent 2011", is lit on the touch screen.
A single press and a paper with a number comes out of the device.
You don't have time to read your number "157" as your number is already starting to light up on the big screen under the topit of the waiting room.
In a split second, it's your turn.
After a short moment, an old couple arrives to inquire about the rent, but the new rents do not seem to concern the people in the waiting room.
The majority of people have come to solve common problems like everywhere else - claims for repairs, insurance events and so on.
In the Ostrava region, people from more than 44,000 apartments in the RPG portfolio have been receiving mail with the new leases in their mailboxes since about mid-November.
RPG Byty offers rent increases of 15 to 38 percent.
The special counter for new rents has been open to the public since November 18.
“It’s been working for almost a week, so it’s still in the test,” the employee behind the desk responds after a moment of hesitation when the client shows up as a journalist.
The deregulation and former miners' apartments of Bakal are a very sensitive local subject.
The vice-president of the parliament and native of the Ostrava region Lubomir Zaoralek of the Social Democrats reported quite strongly before the elections and this is now filling the local newspapers.
“Twenty years later, I want a new floor.”
"They didn't even change me a put...n board in the toilets, relieves in introduction the man mentioned.
However, it is mostly, according to the employees, retirees who come to be sure that they will receive a discount on the new rent price if they now sign as promised RPG in a special offer.
This is a discount of half the amount of rent that will be received by other tenants who have signed their new contract before December 15.
But the "deregulation" window on Havirovaska Street is really not overwhelmed by questions.
"Of the 360 customers who came yesterday, only 40 to 50 came for rent," the employee said at the counter.
And yet RPG offers both on its website and in the windows of individual interviews on rents when necessary.
If the two parties do not agree on the rent, an independent court will make the decision.
"This is not about threats but only about informing about the unique and legitimate way to act legally," RPG said on its website.
"Here no one will go to court," one of the employees of RPG Byty thinks and the man in the street in front of the customer center gives her reason.
“I have 13,000 crowns of retirement and I have 5,000 crowns left to eat, I don’t have enough to go to court,” he says.
The employee suddenly feels uncomfortable.
"We'll see."
"Mr. Zaoralek in the media asks that no one sign and therefore people are waiting," she said.
Rent regulation ends in the Czech Republic at the beginning of 2011 and increases, according to RPG Byty, are an economic necessity.
"And, moreover, the current rents still do not reach the level necessary for the simple maintenance of the housing fund," recalls Pavel Klimes, director of the residential portfolio of the company RPG Byty, that it is precisely the negligence of the housing fund that makes the tenant angry is the main reason for the increase in the rent.
However in 5 years between 2005 and 2010 RPG was able with rents invest in apartments 4 billion, in four years from 2011 to 2014 this should make 5.2 billion.
The large screen hanging from the ceiling in front of the upholstered armchairs in the waiting room on Havirosvka Street, however, repeats some information indicated in red.
"The increase in rent in 2011 is 15 percent and concerns no less than 31,200 apartments or more than 90 percent of RPG apartments."
"And it will always be at most 7.50 CZK per m2 per month," the screen reads.
The 38 percent increase concerns only 400 apartments in the RPG portfolio.
"In these cases, it is an increase of a really very low sum 19.66 Czech crowns per m2," adds RPG.
Next year the rent will remain the same for 2600 apartments.
RPG Byty promises that deregulation will not cause a radical but gradual increase over 4 to 8 years.
It adds other commitments: all the money from the rent increase (see graph) is returned to the apartments in the form of heating savings - new windows and heating.
Those who sign the agreement on rent increases have priority.
The nursery school is also part of the offices included the architects.
the Avriopoint administrative building in Brno is the new headquarters of the Arch. Design company.
No one could have expected it to also house a mini kindergarten with everything you need - colorful walls, imaginative furniture, toys and finally a miniature playground on the terrace.
Since October of last year, children of Arch. design employees can go there.
The architectural project company Arch. Design. whose workshops have produced a large number of constructions in Brno, has been imagining its mini business kindergarten since the first drafts of the Avriopoint building.
She employs about 90 people, mostly of child-bearing age, and she cared that women architects and project managers could quickly get back to work.
Along with reduced-time employment contracts, kindergarten is a bonus offered to its employees by the Arch. Design company as part of its social program.
Builders and architects have the opportunity to combine work that takes care of children.
It was the employees of Arch.Design themselves who designed this kindergarten and with the support of the management they were able to obtain an endowment from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs.
The kindergarten is financed by the European Social Fund through the Human Resources Operational Programme and the State Budget of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to the funding allocations (up to 2.8 million Czech crowns), they were able to buy equipment and devices and after two years ensure a qualified staff as well as the start-up.
After the use of the funding endowment (two years) the company Arch. Design. has the obligation after 3 years to operate the mini kindergarten on its own funds.
The preparation of the project took a year and it was the Economy rating company that helped to apply for staffing.
The care of the children is provided by qualified staff, all day a nurse and a kindergarten teacher take care of the children. children can go to kindergarten without age limitation but they are over three for the most part.
As it is a "mini kindergarten" there can be only 5 children present at the same time, but during the day there are more who replace themselves.
The school operates flexibly according to the needs of the parents and the children of all employees have the same right to use this school without regard to the hierarchical position.
Although it is a matter of individual care and education, the mini kindergarten curriculum is comparable to that for preschool education.
Children do not only play there but also ensure a quality education - from the beginning to the preparation for school benches we teach English.
The classroom is equipped not only with imaginative toys and games but also a computer that children can use.
The presence of small children in society creates a friendly and positive environment.
Parents can at any time control their child and not have the stress of being late to pick up the children at a school far from the parents' workplace.
Parents therefore use their working time in the most productive way.
No wonder there is a natural relationship of loyalty between the employee and the employer.
Arch.Design.s is listed among the companies that offer a bonus of choice for the recruitment of new employees and that are friendly towards the family and through this program strengthens the marketing of HR.
The bone house still fascinates after 100 years. Take a look at Gaudi's interiors.
The roof resembles the back of a prehistoric saurian, the staircase resembles a dinosaur spine and the balconies resembles open fish mouths.
This is the house Casa Battlo in Barcelona by the architect Antoni Gaudi.
Due to its organic shapes, the house has received from the locals the nickname Bone House.
Organic shapes, wild colours, unusual use of stones, fragments of tiles and mosaic, a façade reminiscent of scales and curves everywhere present, that is all that is epic for Antoni Gaudí's Art Nouveau.
The front of the house unfolds its dream lines, pleasant colors and textures that recall nature and animals.
During a more detailed observation we see the geometry, the rhythm and the order thought with precision.
At night the facade of the house becomes even more dramatic and is lit in such a way that the impression of brightness of the colors is reinforced.
The winding and twisting of the shapes also appears in the interiors with the same measure.
The wood copies in waves the window frames, the balustrades, the decorative elements of the doors, the eyelet and the slats.
The house Battlo which stands in the Eixample district in the shopping street Passeig de Gracia at number 43, was born from the construction of a house of 1877 by the architect Emilio Sala Cortes.
The reconstruction took two years and the house was completed in 1906.
The investor, Joseph Battlo, a wealthy entrepreneur, first insisted on the demolition of the old building and the construction of an entirely new one but quickly accepted Gaudí's idea of an unusual and cheaper reconstruction.
But the idea of Casa Battlo as a multi-housing house was not conceived by Gaudí alone.
The architect Josep Maria Jujol worked with him.
It was precisely on his project that the decorations for an apartment representing the owner of the building and the use of the mosaic for the facade were born.
For the facade also worked other artists and creators.
The joint work for the plans of the Casa Battlo house began with a successful cooperation between Jujol and Gaudí.
Jujol participated in the construction of Gaudi's Casa Mila and the Park Guell in which there are other works by Gaudi.
The locals nicknamed the house hot right after its finishing because of its organic shapes "the Bone House".
Others, in view of the specific mechanism of opening the windows, have called it "the house that bails".
It is said that at the top of the building there is a sword similar to that of Saint George the patron of Catalonia.
Other sculpture elements of the building contain hidden religious motifs.
Gaudí thought for the house a system unique in its time of central heating, with ventilation vents and typical fireplaces.
Their inclination of 45 degrees seems strange.
During the creation Gaudi absolutely did not comply with the construction directives of the time and did not let himself be hindered by them.
At the beginning of the construction he obtained from the city the permit to build, knowing, of course, that the data carried on the reconstruction plans were so vague that two years later during the completion the municipal council was horrified and asked for changes.
For example, the members of the city council did not like the fact that the pillars of construction were standing on the public sidewalk.
There was never any change, but, on the contrary, only 15 days after the call of the city Josep Battlo requested (and obtained satisfaction) the authorization to rent the two highest floors.
The owner moved to the lower floors.
In the gallery on the second floor there was a common living room and on the third a bedroom and a private part of the apartment.
The ground floor was rented to a jewellery store.
The entire six-storey house is shared by a staircase through which one accesses to an independent roof terrace.
All right angles and straight lines were cancelled by the basic elements of the reconstruction and replaced by curved walls.
Gaudi also worked on the modern concept of connecting spaces.
The common part can be completely connected by opening the doors of the lounges and the high society can communicate comfortably or limit the private space for more intimate maintenances.
The house with Gaudi's reconstruction received in addition to new facades a non-traditional roof and two additional floors.
Gaudi’s play with light is also impressive, with blue and white glazed tiles with which the inner courtyard is decorated and with skylights.
The two-color set gives maximum light in all floors of the house.
It was simply enough to bet on the principle that white reflects more than dark, which instead absorbs the rays of the sun.
The Casa Battlo house which was inscribed in 2005 in the Unesco World Heritage Fund can be visited by everyone.
On the first floor of the house is the most spacious and splendid apartment accessible to the public.
The owners decided to take this step in 2002 on the occasion of the 150th anniversary of the birth of the famous creator.
They continued the visits as they found it to be a lucrative business and they expanded the scope of visits to the common areas and attic including roof terraces.
The entrance ticket to the monument is really not expensive and costs 16.50 euros; students, pensioners, groups and tourist card holders have 20 percent discount.
The sum is still above the price of admission to other Gaudi buildings in the city.
If you want to feel the real atmosphere of the house with its fantastic turrets, you must quickly find a comrade among the inhabitants of the building and visit the house completely.
How to choose a mattress and a bed base: women have other criteria than men.
No ostentatious frame, but rather the quality of the surface reserved for bedtime, so the mattress and the bed base give a real basis for a good bed.
They must of course complement each other harmoniously to please a specific user.
During the choice several things are decisive,:weight, height, age, health status as well as the sex of the owner.
The type of interior in which you will place the mattress and the base is also important.
A typical example?
For example in the country house where one does not sleep continuously latex mattresses are not appropriate because they "warm up" gently.
They also have a higher weight than standard polyurethane mattresses.
It is necessary to return them frequently.
If they also do not have enough ventilation channels at the heart and if they remain, in addition, on a solid board, they retain moisture. Mold can also form there.
Habit is also decisive in the choice.
Those who spend time abroad, where very thick mattresses are frequently used with a softening layer, will find it difficult to feel good on a low and hard surface.
"This is how all hockey players who come back from the NHL complain that they can't sleep there."
“For their tired shoulders, feet and ribs, they needed mattresses with a softening layer of lazy foam.”
"Such mattresses are also recommended for people who suffer from diabetes who have a nervous system disorder that therefore misassumes the 'information' of the joints and skin," explains Sylva Adamczikova who specializes in upholstered furniture.
That is why a few years ago the mattress with lazy foam conquered hockey players as well as other customers.
"Today everything works well, Tempur, the Italian Magnifex but also the Czech Tropico have for example suitable mattresses.
You don’t have to be an NHL guy to be able to enjoy lazy foam.
This "miracle" simply works.
It optimizes its rigidity and shape depending on the heat absorbed or adapts to the heat of your body.
Nothing puts pressure on you and you will not turn around in the night as after a difficult match.
You just sleep better.
Lazy foam also works as a protection against squares.
For the choice of the mattress according to your size, add the length of the feet, which is about 21/34 cm.
A man and woman with a height of 180cm therefore need a bed of 210/220 cm.
The minimum width for each for a double bed should be 90 cm or 180 cm in total.
For single beds, singles for example, it is recommended to take at least 120 /140 cm.
It is convenient in case of a visit.
'However, there is a simple rule for the width of the bed: when you are lying on your back you should lay your hands comfortably with your elbows slightly bent. Helena Prokopova, President of the Association of Butlers-maids and decorators who has been dedicated for several years to the issue of healthy sleep and ergonomics of furniture and specializes in schools.
For a double bed each needs its own box spring and mattress, so be careful however during the achat to choose the height of the mattress well.
Otherwise you will only have to mount the box spring at different heights and this is not achievable on all bed frames.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, spring mattresses at least 15 cm, from this count for the layer of shape and ventilation at least three centimeters.
"When touching or sitting on the mattress, you should not feel the springs," warns Helena Prokopova.
Each mattress requires a well-defined type of bed frame.
The bed base, when the mattress and the bed base are joined like Siamese sisters, has nothing to do in the bedrooms.
The mattresses ventilated very badly; it should not be washed, which is commonly done today.
And since during the night we normally sweat from 0.2 to 0.75 l of sweat it is clear that after 5/7 years, the mattress begins to recall a large (and clogged) sieve.
For this reason, specialists refuse to advertise a lifespan of 25 years for a mattress or a lifetime warranty.
But everything to its but.
And for this an experience advice from the sellers: for a mattress of 120/140cm, give up, for the upholstery of the mattress, hygiene or washing but instead add a protective mattress that you can easily remove and wash.
And even if nowadays it is common to manufacture coatings with zipper for the whole set, that is to say that after the opening we have two parts (for washing and the size of the washing machine it is very important!) otherwise the handling for large models (and for a single person) becomes when they are removed a fight between a light weight and a heavy weight on a ring.
Do you have a rigid board in your bed instead of a box spring?
Never! Never!
Maximum for a bed for visitors for one night only.
However, equip the board (if there are no) with ventilation holes and use the spring mattress with a minimum height of 15cm with bag springs (from Germany Taschenfederken) and an ventilation layer.
A polyurethane mattress should not be part of such a bed.
For slatted beds with a single position with 14/18 slats, latex mattresses or so-called sandwiches (perhaps the combination of latex and coconut), are ideal but it will always be better for you to have a mattress with more slats, 28 and above, where the slats are folded in the part of the kidney as well as regularity is possible.
For multi-position mattresses you should not take spring mattresses because it does not respond to changes in position.
In addition to the adjustment of the stiffness of the slats, what is called a shoulder cradle can also be installed.
This is a special connection of the slats that allows the slat to be pressed or even tilted so that the shoulder of the sleeper "integrates" well.
For men who have “shoulders as wide as their backs,” this is really an important thing.
This thing is already considered by mattress manufacturers who for "males" have started to use a softening area at shoulder level.
But they also think of women - they again offer them a softer surface at the hips.
For the most difficult customer there are wing or wafer frames with what is called a multi-force suspension.
The pressure spreads to more points and thins the tension.
But of course, beware, as soon as you use a bad pillow (large and swollen with air) on good mattresses and springboard, the "plus" disappears.
The basic rule is a very simple pillow: the pillow must support the head and its tips must reach only the shoulders, so that the shoulder muscles can rest.
The recommended size is 50X60 cm which Scandinavians for example prefer.
When lying on one's side, the pillow should level (with the shoulder cradle of the springboard or the softened area in the mattress) the height of the shoulders.
Modern mattresses still have something in common with the early straw and grass mattresses.
Manufacturers still use natural materials or mixtures.
The trend is also for organic mattresses.
Petroleum-based raw materials, from which polyurethane is made, are replaced by natural oils, such as soybean oil.
Almost all known manufacturers use soybeans.
"The Bio qualification for mattresses means that the heart is made from natural products," explains Petr vasicek of Tropico Plus company.
Natural materials are also used for mattress coatings; one of the first was aloe vera.
But you can add micro-capsules that develop scents of forest or lavender.
There are differences between men and women.
While the birch plant extract so that the mattress coating absorbs heat and cools the body, "cools" the man, the coatings "warms" the women.
Red pepper extract accelerates blood circulation and is therefore warmer for the weaker sex.
The current favorites?
Mattresses made from cold foam (it has more pores with a disrupted cellular structure therefore more breathable than standard polyurethane and has more elasticity.
The combination of different rigidities of cold foams gives polyzone mattresses that know precisely where the head, lower back and feet are.
You will pay for a quality mattress from 7000 crowns and more.
Those who are characterized by their parameters for health have less VAT and are taken as instruments for health.
In the Czech Republic, Gumotex reached the first place.
Saving for the mattress and the sommier is not easy.
From time to time, two mattresses may be provided as part of special actions by manufacturers or producers for the price of one mattress.
For example, the company Magniflex offers Duofreeze mattresses with Memory foam sewn to the coating for 11990 crowns.
The second one can be taken for free.
The era of lazy or viscoelastic foams with an open cell structure and a large thickness was started with the Tempur material at a "cosmic" rate.
This began as a matter for NASA because astronauts were suffering from the start of enormous load factors.
Tempur softens in the heat and hardens, on the contrary, in the cold.
It therefore adapts perfectly to the warm human body and distributes optimal pressure to it.
This is why it is ideal against sleeping pain and for increased comfort during sleep.
Viscoelastic foams are used not only for mattresses but also for health products, such as special foot cushions that relieve the legs and venous system.
Czech manufacturers use, for example, EucathermC or Twinsaver foam or the same type.
Devices to track people are increasingly in demand by parents who want to monitor their children.
Fear for their child leads more and more people to think about monitoring them through a GPS.
The system, originally set up to search for cars, can also be used to trace the movement of people and to help in some cases, such as that of little Anicka Janatkova.
The instrument is currently as big as a matchbox but will soon be the size of a watch.
The case of little Anicka moved a large number of people and they began to look for ways to better protect their children.
Even if the price is to disturb their privacy.
"We are trying to tell everyone that this is not espionage but only another way to decrease the likelihood of another tragedy," said Petr Pilin of the company Macro Weil, one of the suppliers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
"I confess that there may be cases of misuse of such devices, such as putting it in the bag of someone who is not aware, but I have not yet encountered such cases."
“The majority of people are customers who actually buy the product for safety reasons,” Pilin adds.
According to him, children should always know for what purposes the "box" is used and how to use it in an emergency.
The child psychologist, Dana Bockova, draws attention to the fact that if the child does not want to wear such a thing on him, he will get rid of it.
“And even the little ones can show great creativity when it comes to deliberately getting rid of something when they don’t want to be under control.”
“Mobile phones, which can cut like these tracing devices, have already led parents to long waits,” Bockova says.
According to her, the fact that this type of device can help in case of aggression is highly questionable.
"If it is a planned abduction, the perpetrator will do everything possible to ensure that the child does not have an electronic device that can locate him."
“At the moment, it’s the phone.”
"As soon as the tracing devices are developed, they (criminals) will also look for them because the sale will be supported by an advertising campaign."
"In such cases the criminals will always be ahead of the police," says the psychologist.
She admits, however, that such devices can help during an unprepared assault by a pedophile.
According to Robert Cech of RC Monitoring, which offers tracking services for both cars and people, having this type of device can help, even if it is destroyed in the event of an assault.
"The apparatus may be configured in such a way that it is in regular emission after a specified period."
"In the event that the device is destroyed, it still remains the last position of the person concerned."
"The more expensive devices also have an inclinometer that immediately signals the position of the person who has slipped and finds himself in the lying position without moving," Cech said.
According to him, the so-called smart mobile phones that are equipped with a navigation system, can offer a comparable service after having formatted it with a special pro-software.
The problem with today's tracing systems is that they are either similar to pendants the size of a matchbox or smaller telephones.
We can always lose them.
According to Pilina of the company Macro Weil, this is why tests are currently being conducted to make devices that look like common digital watches.
"This will have the advantage that the potential aggressor will not be able to recognize the tracing device."
"Or he will realize it after a while, which will have given the police a little more time," he added.
Whether the tracing device is developed in the form of a bracelet or pendant, it will always use the same technology as for tracing cars.
It is a combination of position acquisition systems using GPS (which is commonly used in self-navigation) and a cell phone function that alerts a vehicle to its current position.
