“The good news is that dogs are fine,” Whitmore says.
"They're in good shape."
"They have been returned to their legitimate owners."
Whitmore declined to say precisely where the dogs had been found, in what neighborhood and under what circumstances they were discovered.
"An investigation is underway."
“We don’t want to say it,” Whitmore said.
"We follow orders."
The dogs' owners, Kristina Rickard and David Peek, could not be reached to provide a comment Thursday.
They were reunited Wednesday afternoon with their two Akitas at a County Animal Shelter located in Downey.
The sheriff's deputies found the van and the two dogs separately in Compton.
The Akitas - Trace, a 3-year-old male, and Didi, a 10-month-old female - were safe, authorities said.
