"In my case, I'm looking for fights everywhere, because for those who don't like the ground game present in mixed martial arts, competitions are rare in North America."
Recently, he who works as a security officer and as a clerk for UPS has delivered bad news to his rivals, winning two gold medals at the World Karate and Kickboxing Association (WKA) Amateur World Championship, from October 23 to 30, in Edinburgh, Scotland.
