A 10-year-old child ingested 81 different chemical substances in one day, according to a study published Wednesday by the association Generations Futures (ex-Movement for the rights and respect of future generations).
The association, which warns that its results "have no statistically significant value in relation to the small number of samples analyzed, but are illustrative of the problem treated", bought between July and September the foods usually consumed in four meals and a snack in one day by a child of ten years, in supermarkets of the Oise and Paris.
